# Backend Fastify Rules

- All ingest endpoints must be implemented as Fastify routes with an explicit JSON Schema on the route definition.
- The route schema is mandatory and must validate the full payload contract:
  - required `sessionId`, `sentAt`, `events`
  - strict event unions for `mouse`, `scroll`, `idle`
  - numeric constraints such as `percent <= 100`
- Never trust `request.body` shape without schema validation; invalid payloads must be rejected automatically with `4xx`.
- Keep the request path fast: acknowledge valid ingest requests immediately with HTTP `200` and a tiny JSON body such as `{"ok":true}`.
- Do not perform slow synchronous work in the request handler.
- Logging must be lightweight and structured through Fastify/Pino; avoid noisy `console.log` per event and never block the event loop with file I/O.
- If persistence is needed, enqueue or hand off work after validation; do not keep the client connection open for downstream processing.
- CORS policy must be explicit. Do not leave production ingest endpoints effectively open to every origin by accident.
- Any backend contract change must be mirrored in the SDK types in the same change.
- All operator/dashboard API endpoints must have `preHandler: [requireOperatorAuth]`. Ingest `POST /api/events` is public.
- Origin validation must use `new URL(origin).origin` for strict comparison — never `startsWith`.
- `siteKey` is required for ingest by default. `ALLOW_INGEST_WITHOUT_SITEKEY=true` is dev-only.
- Body limit is 256 KB via Fastify `bodyLimit`. Security headers (`X-Content-Type-Options`, `X-Frame-Options`) are set via `onSend` hook.
- Never log raw tokens or full siteKeys. Pino `redact` covers `req.headers.authorization`.

## Dashboard API Routes

- `GET /api/sessions` — list sessions with event counts. Supports `limit` (max 200) and `offset` query params.
- `GET /api/sessions/:sessionId` — session detail with events (up to 5000). Optional `?type=` filter.
- `GET /api/events/live` — Server-Sent Events stream. Broadcasts each batch after persistence. Keep-alive every 15s.
- `GET /api/sessions/:sessionId/conversions` — List conversions with goal name/type.
- `POST /api/goals` — Create goal (name, type, rules, is_primary). Tenant via `X-Tenant-Id` header.
- `GET /api/goals` — List goals for tenant.
- `PUT /api/goals/:goalId` — Update goal.
- `DELETE /api/goals/:goalId` — Soft-delete goal.
- `POST /api/conversions` — Server-side conversion registration (requires `sessionId` or `visitorId` + `goalId`).
- Dashboard files are served from `dashboard/` under `/dashboard/` prefix via a second `@fastify/static` registration.

## Feature Engineering Pipeline

- `server/features/extractors.js` — modular extractors for each event type (mouse, scroll, click, form, engagement, session, context, cross_session).
- `server/features/store.js` — `computeAndStore(sessionId)` fetches all events, extracts features, upserts into `session_features`.
- `server/features/backfill.js` — batch backfill script for existing sessions (`npm run backfill`).
- Features are recomputed on every batch arrival (fire-and-forget after persistence + SSE broadcast).
- `GET /api/sessions/:sessionId/features` — returns computed ML feature vector for a session.
- Migration 004: `session_features` table with mouse dynamics, scroll behavior, click patterns, form behavior, engagement, session-level, context, and cross-session features.
- Sliding-window aggregation stored as JSONB (1s, 5s, 30s windows for mouse velocity).
